A Reuters investigation revealed the Bill, Hillary and Chelsea Clinton Foundation had misreported millions of dollars in donations from foreign nations . 
  The charity announced it would refile more than five years of tax documents . 
  'It's the Clinton way: raking in millions from foreign governments while making promises about transparency they never intended to keep,' Carly Fiorina said . 
  Ted Cruz and Ben Carson are among the GOP presidential hopefuls calling on the charity to give back the money . 
  The report cast a new shadow over the charity's fundraising practices while Hillary Clinton served as Secretary of State . 
 